Primary use case:\
\'93Firm is short on free inventory for delivery.\'94\
\
Business context:\
In settlement operations, when the firm is short on free inventory for a delivery obligation on T+1 / T+2, operations analysts manually collect information from position, settlement, reference data, and trade/netting systems. They then prepare factual commentary for QMA, the operations email system used by humans to interact with counterparties.\
\
Phase 1 objective:\
Build a reference implementation that uses Google ADK runtime to semi-automate evidence gathering, diagnosis, and draft commentary recommendation, while keeping human-in-the-loop approval.\
\
Important Phase 1 scope:\
1. Development Plane first.\
2. Pure YAML files and properties for defining use case, agents, prompts, workflow, tools, policy, and evals.\
3. Google ADK as the runtime.\
4. CSV-backed mock tools for Phase 1.\
5. data/ directory is the source for all synthetic sample data.\
6. Read data/data_dictionary.csv carefully and treat it as the authoritative field reference.\
7. QMA Draft Tool is deferred. Do NOT build actual QMA send or draft integration in Phase 1.\
8. MCP Plane is deferred. However, design tools so they can later be exposed through MCP and backed by REST APIs.\
9. RAG / pgvector memory is deferred.\
10. Phase 1 memory is session memory only.\
11. Create sessions.md to document session-memory behavior.\
12. Create experience.md as temporary case memory. Later this will move to a key-value store.\
13. Control Plane in Phase 1 should include lightweight human-in-the-loop review/approval.\
14. Add tests, evals, and a Jupyter notebook.\
15. Add SKILLS.md for future Claude Code / Codex contributors.\
\
